  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Uncertainty quantification was performed using a Monte Carlo propagation of material property and geometric tolerances; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to rank input variability, and its findings informed the UQ parameter ranges. The structured sensitivity analysis artefact has not been separately linked as a hasSensitivityAnalysis node; the screening results are summarised narratively within the UQ report.",
