    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is accepted on the basis of conservative static loading assumption, medium model influence, and medium decision consequence. Monte Carlo UQ confirms all three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim that the FEA framework reproduces ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior within pre-established acceptance bounds.",
